	abstract = {Both the business and educational sectors have been significantly impacted by the introduction of conversational bots driven by artificial intelligence, such as ChatGPT and Google Bard. This study aims to give a comprehensive examination of their impact by doing sentiment analysis on user reviews, debates, and comments using the natural language processing (NLP) application 'TextBlob.' TextBlob's goal is to assess the emotions, polarity, and subjectivity present in user-generated content. This content is gathered through feedback systems, interactions at work, and educational forums. The study finds common attitudes, user happiness, perceived accuracy, and the overall impact of various AI systems on learning and productivity outcomes by analysing these textual insights. Because users have reported improved learning experiences and streamlined operations, the results point to a beneficial influence on industrial productivity and educational engagement. But issues with bias, ethical use, and the veracity of the information all surface. By providing a data-driven knowledge of the promise and limitations given by ChatGPT and Bard, this study aids in the development of more effective integration strategies in the industrial and educational sectors.  © 2025 IEEE.},
