	abstract = {The Metaverse, as the image of a stable and immersive virtual ecosystem supported by Virtual Reality (VR), Augmented Reality (AR), Artificial Intelligence (AI), and blockchain technologies, is a significant chance to rethink the way education is delivered in the Indian context. Despite growing digitalization, there are still critical issues of ensuring equitable access, engagement of learners, and personalization, which limit the impact of the existing e-learning approaches. This paper appraises the technological architecture, implementation plan and governance structure that needs to be adopted to support the mass adoption of the Metaverse based education in India. Focus is put on the merging of Web3.0 ideas, decentralized digital identity platforms, and Generative AI, and how these can be used to improve the adaptive learning processes, credentialing, and collaborative virtual learning environments. The suggested Meta-Bharat Model outlines a systematic roadmap, which covers pilot implementation, national level scaling, and long term governance, in line with the already existing digital infrastructure projects like BharatNet. The quantitative results based on a ten-week assessment time frame show that there are quantifiable improvements in the level of learner engagement, knowledge acquisition and cognitive load decreases. Also, the paper explores key ethical, policy, and cybersecurity issues that support sustainable adoption. The paper is culminated with actionable recommendations geared towards the creation of inclusive, resilient and future ready educational Metaverse in India. © 2026 IEEE.},
