	affiliations = {School of Mechanics and Engineering Science, Shanghai University, Shanghai, China},
	abstract = {Traditional Gaokao volunteer recommendation systems in China suffer from three critical limitations: outdated and fragmented data, disjointed workflows, and simplistic decision-making. To address these issues, this paper proposes an intelligent recommendation platform based on AI large language model (LLM) technology, achieving breakthroughs through three core innovations: architectural reform, intelligent decision-making, and humanized interaction. The platform adopts the "RAGFlow+Ollama"framework for local deployment of the DeepSeek model, integrates the Milvus vector database to build a dynamic knowledge base, and incorporates multi-source real-time data including admission policies and employment trends. It ensures privacy security while achieving sub-3-second low-latency responses. Through a chain-of-thought reasoning mechanism, the system parses students' complex needs (e.g., "Physics subject selection + interest in Computer Science + preference for Shanghai") and generates personalized reports including "stretch-match-safety"strategies, major comparisons, and risk assessments. Compared with traditional systems, the recommendation adaptability is improved by 2.3×. Innovatively replacing complex forms with natural language dialogue, the system supports dynamic modeling of over 60 factors and outputs end-to-end analysis covering "university-major-career"links. Tests show that the system can avoid risks such as subject mismatches, increasing the qualified rate of volunteer forms by 37%, and provides a replicable technical paradigm for AI-enabled educational equity.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
