	abstract = {Currently, generative AI technologies like ChatGPT in education has brought great changes by enabling intelligent learning, performing day-to-day tasks and building a society. These tools enable the educator to facilitate processes, alter content so as to encourage activity among learners and address ordinary routine practices such as assessments and timetables. This enables the instructors to spend most of their time on tutoring and or meaningful student interactivity.AI-driven platforms connect educators, students, and experts globally, facilitating knowledge-sharing and collaboration. They also ease curriculum development while making it more accessible to the diverse learners, with text-to-speech tools and real-time translations. The inclusivity further bridges the gap in education with quality resources made available to less privileged communities and ensures equity. Challenges will include data privacy, algorithmic bias, and an over-reliance on technology. Ethical AI use, transparency, and robust regulations may mitigate these. Educators, technologists, and policymakers must collaborate to balance innovation with inclusivity and equity. Generative AI also supports lifelong learning and reskilling, preparing individuals for a dynamic job market. It enhances engagement and understanding by redefining teaching methodologies with tools like virtual simulations and interactive assessments. Thoughtful implementation of AI can reduce educational disparities, support diverse learners, and reshape pedagogy for a digital future. © Grenze Scientific Society, 2025.},
