	abstract = {Intelligent technologies are driving the digital transformation and intelligent upgrade of education, reshaping the future of learning. The rise of generative AI has advanced the development of conversational agents in teaching, learning support, and educational management. Conversational agents are intelligent systems capable of language understanding, reasoning, and generation. They interact with users through natural language and carry out tasks accordingly. This study uses CiteSpace to visualize and analyze related literature from CNKI between 2010 and 2024. It explores the evolution of applications, research hotspots, core institutions, highly cited papers, and development trends in the field of education. The analysis reveals a clear evolution from rule-based chatbots to generative AI-powered conversational systems. Their applications now cover classroom instruction, intelligent assessment, and learning behavior analysis. Current research focuses on AI-enhanced education, smart teaching, and personalized learning. In the future, conversational agents will become more intelligent and adaptive. Attention should also be paid to ethical concerns, the intelligence gap, and educational equity to ensure their quality development and responsible use. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
