	abstract = {The advancement of artificial intelligence technology has enabled large language models to demonstrate significant potential in vocational education, particularly in teaching quality assurance and personalized guidance. This study analyzes the application pathways and pedagogical effectiveness of large language models using the Digital Production and Control Technology course as a case study. Comparative experimental results demonstrate that students receiving large language model-assisted instruction significantly outperformed those receiving traditional teaching methods in academic achievement, learning satisfaction, and learning engagement. Large language models enhanced teaching quality through personalized content recommendation, learning behavior analysis, and intelligent assessment. Their applications encompass instructional assistance, learning analytics, and intelligent evaluation, enabling teachers to acquire resources, monitor student progress, provide feedback, and automatically assess student performance. The research recommends strengthening the application of large language models in vocational education, developing personalized learning resources, and improving learning analytics and feedback mechanisms to enhance vocational engineering education quality.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
