	abstract = {As the field of artificial intelligence experiences robust growth, the resulting shifts in industry and society are significantly altering numerous sectors. The academic program of visual communication design within higher education institutions, which is an interdisciplinary field that merges creative thought, aesthetic sensibility, and technical proficiency, is also being influenced by these emerging technologies. This article addresses the integration of artificial intelligence in nurturing visual communication design expertise and its repercussions on educational frameworks. It begins by presenting an overview of the fundamental principles and historical progression of artificial intelligence, followed by an examination of its role in the four pivotal aspects of visual communication design pedagogy: instructional methods for teachers, the learning processes of students, evaluative measures in education, and academic mentorship. In light of these challenges, educators are encouraged to assimilate artificial intelligence tools into their curricula, enhance teaching strategies through data-driven insights, and fortify the ethical education surrounding technology to advance the evolution of visual communication design education in the contemporary era. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.},
