	affiliations = {Huaibei Institute of Technology, Anhui, Huaibei, 235000, China},
	abstract = {Early childhood education faces significant challenges in developing developmentally appropriate and engaging curricula that meet diverse learning needs, while existing AI-supported curriculum generation approaches often lack the pedagogical rigor and practical implementability required for preschool settings. To address these limitations, we introduce PreEduAI, a novel multi-agent collaborative framework specifically designed for automated preschool curriculum development. The framework employs four specialized agents working in synergy: a Curriculum Designer Agent for content generation, Quality Evaluator Agent for pedagogical assessment, Activity Optimizer Agent for iterative refinement, and Implementation Advisor Agent for practical guidance. We develop the comprehensive STEAM-P evaluation framework encompassing six critical dimensions (Suitability, Teaching Effectiveness, Engagement, Activity Design, Material Integration, and Practicality) to systematically assess curriculum quality across multiple educational aspects. Extensive experiments demonstrate that PreEduAI achieves substantial performance improvements of 7.6-13.8% over state-of-the-art language models including GPT-4.1, Claude-3.5-Sonnet, Llama-3-8B, and Gemini-2.5-Pro, reaching an average STEAM-P score of 7.82. Ablation studies confirm the effectiveness of multi-agent collaboration, with the complete framework showing +0.95 points improvement over baseline performance, establishing new benchmarks for AI-supported early childhood curriculum generation. © 2013 IEEE.},
