	abstract = {With the explosive development of generative AI technology, the graphic design industry is undergoing an unprecedented paradigm shift. As a field within secondary vocational education focused on cultivating frontline skilled professionals [3], graphic design programs are at the forefront of this transformation. They face the daunting challenge of traditional teaching models being overturned, while simultaneously embracing a significant opportunity to reshape talent development systems and elevate educational quality. This paper aims to systematically explore the role of artificial intelligence technology in secondary vocational graphic design programs, as well as its application and development within these programs. The article first reviews the current status of AI technology application in the graphic design field both domestically and internationally, providing a detailed comparative analysis of the core functions and advantages/disadvantages of mainstream AI image generation tools. It then delves into the core challenges currently facing vocational graphic design programs. Based on an assessment of AI technology trends, the paper proposes a systematic solution for vocational graphic design programs to navigate transformation and embrace the future. This solution encompasses multiple dimensions, including AI-enhanced learning, teaching assistance, and the creation of authentic scenarios. The goal is to provide theoretical reference and practical pathways for the modernization of this field.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
