	abstract = {The rapid development of generative artificial intelligence (AI) has exposed structural limitations in traditional integrated circuit (IC) engineering education, where teaching objectives remain focused on low-order cognitive tasks that AI can easily replace. This paper proposes a "coach-assistant"human-AI collaborative teaching paradigm that systematically reconstructs the IC education ecosystem by integrating multi-agent AI systems with electronic design automation (EDA) toolchains, thereby advancing computer technology applications in electronic engineering and promoting efficiency in IC design processes. In the proposed framework, AI is repositioned as an always-available intelligent partner that supports concept formation, design-space exploration, multi-objective optimization, and reflective practice, while instructors shift to facilitating higher-order thinking and learning-process design. Key implementation strategies include: (1) dynamic knowledge graphs for personalized theoretical learning; (2) open-ended performance-optimization competitions to drive inquiry-based experimental teaching; and (3) digital-twin-based visualization of multidimensional learning trajectories, enabling a shift from outcome-oriented to process-oriented developmental evaluation. The paradigm leverages generative AI to enhance EDA workflows, accelerating multi-objective optimization and trade-off analysis in IC design, cultivating compound talents proficient in AI-driven electronic systems.  © 2026 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
