	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105026924005?origin=resultslist},
	affiliations = {Panzhihua University, Sichuan, Panzhihua, China},
	abstract = {This article explores the possibility of using ChatGPT, a transformer-based large language model(LLM), as a digital teaching tool to help improve effective learning of the English language within a college context. To conduct the research study, the mixed-methods design will be used, which will include 200 college students, 20 English teachers, and 10 AI specialists. The study performs a survey, interviews, and classroom observations comparing the traditional way of teaching with the assistance of AI via ChatGPT. The outcomes indicate better writing skills and conversational ability in subjects with ChatGPT, whereas vocabulary learning showed a minor better performance with regular training. Of paramount importance, the present research includes technical specifics of the architecture of ChatGPT and its application in educational systems. We investigate both backend AI technologies, user interface design and opportunities of APIs-based implementation in learning management systems (LMS). Along with the pedagogical advantages, the issues of data privacy and academic integrity still emerge. These results give policy-makers, educators, and technologists a blueprint on how they can integrate AI in higher education ethically. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
