	affiliations = {Alliance University, Bengaluru, Bangalore, India},
	abstract = {Educational systems form a uniquely porous, heterogeneous distributed environment spanning LMS/SIS, research enclaves, dorm networks, and IoT. This article presents a Zero-Trust reference architecture and a phaseable controls stack for identity (WebAuthn, SCIM, senderconstrained tokens), networks (WPA3-Enterprise, NAC/SDN microsegmentation, DDoS engineering), and applications/data (LTI 1.3 hardening, workload identity federation, CMEK, tamper-evident logging, 3-2-1-1-0 backups). The paper operationalizes SecOps via standardized telemetry, ATT&CKaligned detections, SIEM/SOAR playbooks, and institutionlevel SLOs. Digital assessments are secured through ephemeral VDIs, per-student cryptographic artifacts, integrity analytics, and privacy-preserving proctoring. AI/ML risks are treated with retrieval allow/deny lists, output guardrails, provenance, and DP-aware analytics. Governance links NIST/ISO/CIS controls to verifiable evidence. The article concludes with a research agenda on ZK-provable assessment integrity, verifiable LLM guardrails, and PSI+DP benchmarking, robust proctoring datasets, and automated policy-as-code discovery. © 2025 IEEE.},
