	abstract = {This research presents a standardized, automated, and scalable model that incorporates a centralized, AI-assisted Placement Portal to enhance the student placement process. Inconsistencies, manual data handling, and communication delays during placement activities, and duplication of effort can become major challenges when academic institutions need to apply resumes, consider job prospects, assess students' strengths, and track students' readiness across departments. The proposed Placement Portal integrates intelligent functionality to support usability and decision-making with the contemporary uniform web technologies of React, Vite, TailwindCSS, and Supabase for authentication, storage, and persistent data. Students, educators, and placement officers have access to the system securely and according to their defined roles, allowing for job-candidate matching, automatic extraction of skills, structured resume parsing, and oversight mechanized from a single interface. Experimental evidence indicates that the platform enhances data consistency, minimizes time involved with administrative coordination, and improves transparency of placement-related data when compared to manual institutional workflows. The Portal's modular approach makes it a reliable, efficient, and institutionally ready placement automation option that accommodates multiple job types, changing placement policy, and dynamic student needs. Further, the platform facilitates end-to-end placement operations with intelligent assistance functions that include mock interview support, AI-generated assessments, and automated communication, which can move a manual process of disconnected tasks into a cohesive digital ecosystem.  © 2026 IEEE.},
