	affiliations = {Jinan Preschool Education College, Shandong, Jinan, China},
	abstract = {This study examines the development of information literacy among high school teachers within the TPACK framework, grounded in the guiding principle of "Educator Spirit."Drawing on survey data from 354 practicing educators and employing structural equation modeling, the analysis reveals that Technological Knowledge (TK) and Technological Content Knowledge (TCK) serve as primary direct drivers of Technological Pedagogical Content Knowledge (TPACK), while Content Knowledge (CK) and Pedagogical Knowledge (PK) exert their influence predominantly through indirect, mediating pathways. Importance-Performance Map Analysis (IPMA) further confirms TK and TCK as critical dimensions that exhibit both high strategic importance and strong performance outcomes. Building on these empirical findings, the research proposes the AI-Enhanced Teacher Development Spiral (AETDS) - a comprehensive, cyclical model that integrates intelligent diagnostic assessment, personalized instruction enabled by large language models, and authentic, agent-supported teaching practice. By embedding continuous feedback loops and systematically integrating ethical and pedagogical values into professional development processes, AETDS offers a theoretically sound and practically implementable framework for cultivating educators who are not only proficient in digital technologies but also deeply committed to value-driven teaching practices. This study thus contributes robust empirical evidence and a structured, scalable model to support the development of a high-quality, ethically grounded teaching workforce capable of meeting the dynamic challenges of contemporary digital education.  © 2026 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
