	affiliations = {SVKM's NMIMS University, Mukesh Patel School of Technology Management and Engineering (MPSTME), Department of Computer Engineering, Mumbai, India},
	abstract = {The integration of Large Language Models (LLMs) in educational technology has strong potential, but common issues such as factual reliability, computational overhead, and inconsistent automated assessment limit real-world use. We present Meta-Edu, a multi-agent educational system designed to address these challenges with three key innovations:(1) a Retrieval-Augmented Generation pipeline with semantic chunking and re-ranking, ensuring that generated content stays aligned with trusted sources rather than relying purely on model recall; (2) an adaptive meta-classifier that decides when to use lightweight single-pass generation versus more careful iterative refinement, improving efficiency without sacrificing quality; and (3) a confidence-aware evaluation framework that integrates OCR for handwritten or scanned submissions and performs semantic grading with optional human review for uncertain cases.Meta-Edu supports multiple document formats , provides hybrid retrieval with confidence scoring, and includes research intelligence features such as literature clustering and gap analysis. Meta-Edu produced factually reliable content (95.3% accuracy) and graded student work with strong consistency (80% accuracy, 0.524 Kappa) using qwen/qwen3-32b model. In practical classroom and academic evaluation settings, Meta-Edu showed high agreement with human graders and maintained strong factual correctness while reducing unnecessary computation. © 2026 IEEE.},
