	abstract = {WASSCE Lab is an AI-powered exam preparation platform designed to support high school students in West Africa as they prepare for the West African Senior School Certificate Examination (WASSCE). The system addresses educational inequities by providing students in one of the most disadvantaged country with free access to exam preparation. This system allows students to practice using past exam questions that are structured by topic and difficulty. These practices are aligned with the official WASSCE syllabus. In addition to practicing, students receive support from an AI powered chatbot(built using GPT-4o) that acts as a tutor, offering immediate feedback and explanations when students answer questions incorrectly or seek clarification. Based on the hope of providing equitable education, the WASSCE Lab was co-designed with local educators and tailored to the Liberian context. The chatbot is engineered to maintain focus. With support from Liberia's Ministry of Education, the platform is being scaled nationwide and used in public and private schools. WASSCE Lab demonstrates how inclusive, localized AI technologies can empower learners and educators in under-resourced environments. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
