	abstract = {This work-in-progress research-to-practice paper describes EdQuest, a framework designed to enhance the discovery and accessibility of high-quality educational resources. The rapid growth of online educational content presents challenges for students and educators in efficiently locating relevant and credible materials. Traditional search engines often return an overwhelming number of results, many of which lack academic reliability or contextual relevance. EdQuest addresses these issues by leveraging Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning techniques to optimize educational resource retrieval. Research-to-Practice: EdQuest integrates advanced web crawling, large language model (LLM) API integration, and collaborative filtering to refine search results. The system employs Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques, including keyword extraction, semantic analysis, and content summarization, to filter and prioritize relevant educational content. By incorporating collaborative filtering, EdQuest customizes search results based on user interactions, improving resource relevance for students, educators, and researchers. Method of Assessment: The effectiveness of EdQuest is assessed using multiple evaluation metrics, including search accuracy, retrieval efficiency, and user satisfaction. The assessment methods involve tracking user queries and interactions, measuring response times, and evaluating the relevance of retrieved resources through expert validation. Initial usability testing is conducted with students and educators to collect feedback and identify areas for refinement. Findings: Preliminary results suggest that EdQuest significantly reduces the time required to locate relevant educational materials compared to conventional search methods. Early user feedback highlights improvements in search accuracy and content personalization. However, further refinements are necessary to optimize algorithm performance and enhance user experience. Additional evaluation phases will provide deeper insights into the system's effectiveness. Implications: EdQuest has the potential to transform how students and educators access online educational resources by reducing search time and improving content relevance. Future work includes expanding the dataset, refining recommendation algorithms, and integrating adaptive learning techniques to enhance personalization. The findings from this research contribute to the advancement of AI-driven educational technology and resource discovery methodologies. © 2025 IEEE.},
