	abstract = {The emerging bloom in the welcome of the eLearning business has led to a number of such issues coming into existence, and involving the lack of interactivity, the lack of personalization, and real-time support of learners. Like usual, existing systems use conventional content delivery systems, thus reducing the chances of interaction among students, hence burdening teachers with grading, content development, and tracking learners. These are the issues that would provide them with a push in the development of an intelligent. and versatile platform that could simulate a digital experience similar to the classroom to a greater level, and is accommodating. The paper suggests an online lesson powered by AI and using Smart Board technology and Large Language Models (LLMs) that would make an online classroom interactive and personalized. On one side, the Smart Board can be used to collaborate in real time and to actively visualize, and on the other side, it is possible to tutor in real time, provide adaptive feedback, and create intelligent content with LLM usage. This is then optimized using multimodal input processing, adaptive analytics, and cloud scale to improve engagement, teaching, learning, and access. There is some emerging evidence to support the idea that Smart Board interactivity and AI powered customization can greatly improve the learning process and become the foundation of the next generation of eLearning.  © 2025 IEEE.},
