	affiliations = {Mae Fah Luang University, Chiang Rai, Thailand},
	abstract = {This study investigates the use of a generative AI assistant agent to support learning in a virtual reality (VR) game science lab. The system integrates a large language model (LLM) with VR to provide learners with real-time guidance during experiments and to answer content-related questions. Sixty participants were divided into an experimental group, which used the AI-assisted VR game, and a control group, which used the VR game without AI support. Learning outcomes were measured using post-test assessments, and learning engagement was evaluated through a questionnaire covering usefulness, ease of use, and satisfaction. Results show that the experimental group achieved significantly higher scores than the control group, indicating improved knowledge acquisition. In addition, participants in the experimental group reported high levels of engagement, particularly in terms of the usefulness of AI support and overall satisfaction, despite some usability challenges. These findings suggest that integrating an AI agent within VR educational games can enhance both learning performance and learner engagement, highlighting its potential as a promising approach for science education.  © 2025 IEEE.},
