	affiliations = {Transilvania University of Brasov, Eroilor 29, Braṣov, 500036, Romania},
	abstract = {The Programming Examination Platform (PeP) is an innovative system that leverages GPT-4o technology to revolutionize programming exams. This advanced platform generates personalized exam questions on demand, ensuring high security and relevance to each student’s study material. Using AI, PeP creates unique, customized questions for each exam session, enhancing both the security and fairness of the examination process. Accessibility is a key focus of PeP. The platform includes dedicated support for visually impaired students, featuring text-to-speech and speech-to-text functionality. In PeP, traditional exams are task-based and challenge students to demonstrate their coding skills through practical assignments. In contrast, exams for visually impaired students are formatted as multiple-choice questions to accommodate their needs. This distinction ensures that all students, regardless of their abilities, can effectively showcase their knowledge. PeP also implements robust anti-cheat measures, preventing students from exiting the exam or copying content, thus maintaining the integrity of the examination. The platform is designed with redundancy and reliability in mind, saving completed exams to a secure database to ensure continuity even if AI services are interrupted. Students benefit from comprehensive feedback, receiving immediate grades and feedback directly from the AI, which facilitates faster learning and improvement. Flexibility is another key feature of PeP, allowing students to resume exams after interruptions and enables supervisors to schedule and manage exams effortlessly. The platform includes a web management interface that allows teachers and proctors to efficiently manage exams and monitor student progress. Through this interface, students can view their results, check their rankings, and book their exams online. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.},
