	abstract = {Learner-centric systems are designed to reduce the stress, anxiety, fear and pressure that students face during the learning and exam preparation process. This research aims to introduce a unified Educator-Student platform with a learnercentric assessment system that can significantly enhance the learning experience by providing detailed personalized support and feedback to learners. The platform enables teachers to upload materials, from which learning notes, summaries, and quizzes can be automatically generated. It leverages Artificial Intelligence (AI) to create practice questions aligned with the topics students have studied, helping them self-evaluate their preparedness. The system can also assess student answers, assign marks, and deliver positive affective feedback for each question in real time. The platform offers features such as customized study materials, quiz management, performance tracking, and automated feedback delivery. It is designed to address the challenges faced by students, such as a lack of motivation, anxiety, and fear of challenging tasks, which can often lead to academic boredom due to negative feedback, delays, and a lack of specificity in feedback, as well as higher cognitive overload resulting from challenging and poorly presented instructional materials. It is developed using a combination of Bloom's Taxonomy, Large Language Models (LLMs), Prompt Engineering, Declarative Selfimproving Python (DSPy), and technology adoption strategies. Upon testing with sample texts, the system was found to generate good-quality quizzes, accurately evaluate responses, and deliver precise, targeted feedback, demonstrating its effectiveness and efficiency. © 2025 IEEE.},
