	abstract = {The concept of Education 5.0 has emerged as a response to the rise of Information and Communication Technology (ICT), especially Artificial Intelligence (AI), which has established a significant niche in education. This paper elaborates on two areas of AI that have been used to revolutionize higher education in teaching and learning: Machine Learning (ML) and Generative AI (GAI). In particular, we discuss the applications of ML in predicting student performance, personalized learning, learning analytics, and plagiarism detection. Additionally, we provide an overview of the applications of GAI in higher education, including AI-powered tutoring, automated content creation, academic writing and research, as well as grading and feedback. Finally, we present challenges and open research problems to guide future research in this area. © 2025 IEEE.},
