	title = {RAG SLIITbot: Sri Lankan Universities Develop AI Tutor Tailored to Unique Teaching Styles},
	year = {2025},
	journal = {ICIIS 2025 - Next-Gen Engineering for Industry 5.0: Innovating Intelligent Systems for Human Centric Future: Proceedings of 2025 IEEE 19th International Conference on Industrial and Information Systems},
	pages = {413 - 418},
	doi = {10.1109/ICIIS69028.2026.11450883},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105036742884?origin=resultslist},
	affiliations = {Sri Lanka Institute of Information Technology, Metro Campus, Faculty of Computing, Colombo, Sri Lanka; Sri Lanka Institute of Information Technology, Northern Uni, Faculty of Computing, Jaffna, Sri Lanka; Sri Lanka Institute of Information Technology, Faculty of Computing, Malabe, Sri Lanka; University of Peradeniya, Department of Computer Engineering, Sri Lanka},
	abstract = {Artificial Intelligence (AI) has enabled personalized learning, but general-purpose chatbots like ChatGPT often lack curriculum alignment. This paper introduces RAG SLIITbot, a specialized AI tutor for Sri Lankan higher education, built on Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to deliver accurate, subject-specific responses grounded solely in lecturer-uploaded materials. The system processes PDF, DOCX, and TXT files through a multimodal pipeline that extracts text and visuals using AI transcription, then generates semantic embeddings via OpenAI models stored in a Pinecone vector database. Leveraging LangChain for orchestration, Pinecone for indexing, and GPT-4 for generation, RAG SLIITbot delivers responses through a Streamlit interface. Evaluated on ten software engineering queries, it achieved 92% accuracy and 90% curriculum specificity, significantly outperforming ChatGPT (70% accuracy, 60% specificity), with differences confirmed by the Wilcoxon signed-rank test (p < 0.01). A rubric-based assessment showed high inter-rater reliability (Cohen's Kappa k = 0.87). User surveys of 50 students and 10 lecturers reported 88% overall satisfaction, with 92% rating ease of use and 89% curriculum relevance positively. RAG SLIITbot reduces hallucinations, ensures content fidelity, and supports student-centered learning in resource-constrained settings, demonstrating how domain-specific AI tutors can be effectively tailored to local educational needs. © 2026 IEEE.},
