	affiliations = {Universidad Carlos Iii de Madrid, Dept. Telematic Engineering, Leganés, Madrid, Spain},
	abstract = {This research category full paper provides new insights into the behavior of Generative Artificial Intelligence (AI) for question generation. Generative AI is considered very useful for supporting students and teachers can also use them during the teaching process, e.g. for generating questions. In this line, the purpose of this work is to analyze the usefulness of Gemini 1.0 Pro for generating multiple-choice and short questions, and particularly evaluate (1) the appropriateness of the questions for the course, exams and the correctness of questions, (2) the differences in quality depending on the question type and (3) course topic, and (4) the effect of the input information in the quality of questions. For this work, two engineering courses about programming and cybersecurity are considered. Results show that the quality of generated multiplechoice questions is higher than short questions in all the evaluated aspects in (1). Moreover, questions are found to be appropriate for the course in general, although the suitability for exams is improvable. Furthermore, the inclusion of the syllabus and previous exam questions in the prompts of Gemini barely improve the appropriateness of the questions and answers but they significantly improve the suitability for exams. These results show the potential of Generative AI for content generation, considering certain limitations. © 2025 IEEE.},
