	abstract = {Against the strategic backdrop of national educational digital transformation and the 'New Liberal Arts' initiative, this study addresses the structural tension between technological empowerment and the weakening of critical thinking within animation education. It not only constructs a generative AI-empowered pedagogical model for cultivating higher-order thinking skills but also innovatively proposes a three-dimensional framework encompassing 'Goal-Operation-Evaluation.' The research establishes a progressive pathway characterized by 'Cognitive Restarting - Logical Deconstruction - Value Reconstruction'. An empirical study involving 120 animation majors at a university (September 2024 - January 2025) confirmed that the model effectively mitigates the issue of narrative dilution caused by technological dependency. It provides a replicable assessment and intervention strategy for cultivating artistic talent in the intelligent era, offering significant theoretical value and practical implications for advancing disciplinary innovation in 'Artificial Intelligence + Arts Education.' © 2025 IEEE.},
