	abstract = {This paper proposes and tests an Intelligent Teaching Assistant (ITA) based on the Large Language Model (LLM) and aimed at the effectiveness of the learning process in the digital education space. By using the natural language processing and generation potential of LLMs, the presented ITA will offer the interactive dialogue with students, real-time explanations, and personal feedback that is tied to the learning progress of a particular student. It was built atop a fine-tuned LLM that was trained on curated academic text and thus it is able to answer a vast number of subject-specific questions correctly as well as adjust its answers to the proficiency level of the learner. Architecture combines conversational interface and real-time analytics to monitor the learner behaviour, knowledge gaps, and engagement levels. The participants were separated into two parties: one who tried the learning based on the assistant of the LLM and the other who studied the traditional way. Evaluation would be done in terms of pre assessment scores, post assessment scores, times on-task analysis and user satisfaction questionnaires. The findings showed that the ITA group improved remarkably in conceptual acquisition and knowledge retention than the control group. © 2025 IEEE.},
